The Akwa Ibom State government is set to unveil a nine-point guideline for hospitality and allied services operations as part of measures to curb the spread of COVID-19. The unveiling ceremony, slated for tomorrow, is to be anchored by the Ministry of Culture and Tourism, House of Assembly Committee on Tourism, Akwa Ibom State Chapter of Federation of Tourism Association of Nigeria (FTAN) and the Association of Hotel Proprietors. A statement by the Chairman, Publicity Subcommittee of the event, Mr. Godwill Enyedok, on behalf of the Chairman, Akwa Ibom State Hospitality Monitoring Team (AK-HMT), Mr. Ini Akpabio, said the ceremony will hold at the Ibom Hotel and Golf Resort, Uyo.